## In the world of software, almost everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

The software WILL play music and follow the user's requests accurately.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

Adding visuals such as pause/play button.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

Have something fairly similar to a music streaming platform (just much more limited in terms of song choices).

## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?

We will need to shape our overall skills to achieve this. Something that I need to focus on is randomizing the output. We will need to also find the songs that will be used and finish deciding on the genres. We will both do our contribute on ensuring that the "artistic" (music) is done and that the software is up and running.
